z^3 &= 1 \\[6pt]
z^3 &= \cos 0 + {\mathrm{\hspace{0.05em}i}\mkern 1mu}\sin 0 \hspace{5.2em}\end{aligned}z3z3​=1=cos0+isin0​Hence, using de Moivre's theorem, we getz=(cos⁡0+isin⁡0)13=cos⁡(2kπ3)+isin⁡(2kπ3)[fork=0,1,2]\begin{aligned}
